            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Hello,\n\nAs per my understanding `__init__.py` should be present for a directory to be python module. Only then can we refer to the internal modules using `module.<internal_module_filename>`\n\nIt would certainly help if there is a directory view of the files during the configuration step.\nOther details like Upper case keys are mentioned in the section above: http://flask.pocoo.org/docs/0.10/config/#configuring-from-files\n\nI would be happy to submit a PR for adding missing info about the directory in the example mentioned in the doc, if anyone else agrees.\n"
